## Git & PR workflow

- One tracked issue per unit of work; **search before starting** — never open a parallel
  branch for an in-progress topic.
- All PRs target `<FILL: main>`. Small, atomic, one concern. **Squash-merge, delete the
  branch.** Never push directly to the trunk or production.
- Branch names: `<FILL: feature/… | fix/… | refactor/… | chore/…>`.
- WIP cap: `<FILL: ≤5>` branches/PRs in flight; stale (no PR in 14 days) → open or delete.

## Definition of done

Merged is **not** done. A change is done only when: acceptance criteria demonstrated · an
automated test covers it (a bug fix has a fail-before/pass-after regression test) ·
verified observable in the running system · no unexplained complexity increase · security
invariants preserved · branch deleted, issue closed. **Claims must be git-verifiable** —
report from `git log`/`gh pr view`, never from intent.

